        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 31 at 2:43PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 242 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Pinos Altos. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Silver City, Pinos Altos, Cobre, Bayard, Hanover, Fierro, North
Hurley, Santa Clara, Fort Bayard, Arenas Valley, Little Walnut
Village, and Ben Lilly Memorial.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
